
[1]demerit

   DEMERIT, n. [ L. To earn or deserve.]

   1. That which deserves punishment, the opposite of merit; an
   ill-deserving; that which is blamable or punishable in moral conduct;
   vice or crime.

   2. Anciently, merit; desert; in a good sense.

                DEMERIT, v.t. To deserve blame or punishment.
